Boil a full #kettle{}.

While it boils, heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, fry the @sliced mushrooms{180%grams}, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Meanwhile, pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Boil the @spaghetti{180%grams}, ~{8%minutes}.

In the meantime, stir the @creme fraiche{150%grams}, @vegetable stock paste{10%grams} and @water{75%milliliters} into the mushrooms. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat. Simmer, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Next, add the @baby spinach{40%grams} to the sauce in handfuls, making sure it's piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once the pasta is cooked, drain. Stir the cooked pasta, @butter{20%grams} and half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%grams} into the sauce. Taste and season with salt and pepper. Add a splash of water if it's too thick.

Share the pasta between your bowls. Sprinkle with the remaining cheese and the @truffle zest{1%sachet}. Top with the @wild rocket{20%grams} and drizzle with the @balsamic glaze{12%milliliters} to finish. Enjoy!

